JOB DESCRIPTION
- Min 2 years and above experience in IT industry as developer/release related roles;
- Hands-on experience in SVN, Hudson/Jenkins, branching/ merging practical skills;
- Basic Knowledge of development in core Java, J2EE, Oracle or other relational database and SQL scripting, Javascript;
- At least one scripting language (shell, Perl, Python, etc);
- Good technical writing skills;
- Fluent in English; 
JOB DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES
- Work with developers and supporting team to sustain release process efficiently;
- Follow the release processes and policy strictly;
- Conduct release conflicts review with developers to ensure merging quality;
- Support continuously integration mechanism improvement;
- Regularly review and improve release tasks, from all related aspects, automated processes, tools, processes;
- Manage deployments and environments for QA testing;
- Code branching and merging control.
- Server services management.

Responsibilities (職位描述)
1、負責BI專案的建設需求調研、業務溝通及研發實施；
2、負責海量資料存儲/計算框架的設計與開發, 根據業務需要, 進行資料建模, 創建OLAP多維分析框架, 設計、開發、優化和維護ETL工具和流程;
3、負責資料開發、資料應用所需工具的設計、實現, 説明業務分析團隊通過資料產品, 系統化、自動化的提升業務分析效率;

1) 精通Linux 系統相關知識,有至少三年以上主流Linux (CentOS 6, CentOS 7, Debian等) 使用經驗;
2) 熟悉Linux的高可用性, 集群和分散式系統架構,部署和維護;;
3) 至少熟悉兩種指令碼語言，如GO, Ruby, Shell, Bash, Perl, Python語言等
4) 熟悉Web相關技術，包括Tomcat,Apache,Nginx等開源軟體管理,配置和優化;
5) 熟練掌握資料庫MySQL, Postgres（最好瞭解TSDB）部署,性能調優,高可用;
6) 熟悉VMware, KVM, Docker等;
7) 熟悉Puppet, cfengine, Chef等;
8) 參與項目需求分析, 完成相關系統方案設計
9) 部署和維護開源平臺的軟體和系統和支援現有運營的Linux企業系統
10) 服從領導安排的其他工作, 完成上級領導指定的其他工作任務

This role is responsible for applying IT Project Management knowledge, skills, tools and techniques to IT Project activities insuring projects are delivered within scope, budget and timelines. 

Job Description: 
1.Strategy
Support the deployment of IT Project Delivery tools, methodologies and standards.
2.Business Partner
·         Build strong working relationships with the Country Business Unit and IT teams;
·         Support the IT Program Leads in leading the project management processes for potential new business;
·         Contribution to improving the country business unit P&L through effective usage of IT services and solutions;
3.Project Delivery
·         Responsible for managing large IT projects from definition phases through to successful delivery.  Average project size (<€1m);
·         IT budget management – control project costs, deliver within budget;
·         Prepare and maintain the project plan and time scales – control project time-scales, deliver on time;
·         Preparation of timely and accurate PMO reports;
·         Resource management and development – direction, motivation, training and decision support to project staff;
·         Recognize and manage differing skill sets, performance and conflicts;
4.Business Development
·         Support project management activity for new business initiatives. 
5.Customer / Supplier Management 
·         Establish productive business relationships with all customers and suppliers as appropriate;
·         Implementation of Project Delivery standards in line with global policy;
·         Risk Management;
·         Change Management;
·         Project Planning;
·         Project Budgeting;
·         Test & Training Management;
·         Implementation Management;
·         Resource Management.
6.People Management
·         Management and development of project resources – ensuring the skills requirements of the project are met and understood;
·         Communication – contribute to the effective communication structure in place i.e. weekly / monthly team meetings.

